An Akure Chief Magistrate’s Court has remanded one Alesanmi Iwanefun to the Nigeria Correctional Centre in Ondo State for allegedly killing his brother, Orimisan, with a pestle. Alesanmi, aged 30, was said to have committed the offence on January 24, 2021, around Madagbayu street, Kiribo in the Ondo State Magisterial District. He reportedly hit his brother with a pestle during a fight. Police prosecutor, Inspector Taiwo Oniyere, informed the court that the offence was contrary to sections 316 and punishable under section 319(1) of Criminal Code Cap 37 Vol1 Laws of Ondo State of Nigeria 2006. The plea of the accused person was not taken when he was arraigned because he had no legal representation. Presiding Magistrate, O. L. Abu, directed the prosecutor to duplicate the case file and send the same to the office of the Director of Public Prosecution (DPP) for legal advice. He adjourned further hearing of the case to March 8, 2021. The Nation By Chinyere Omeire Lagos - A 49-year-old electrician, Ismaila Salau,on Tuesday in an Igbosere High Court denied killing his wife, Silifat Yakubu with a pestle. Salau was arraigned in 2015, on a count charge of murder preferred against him by the Lagos State Government. At the resumed hearing, the witness… In "News" A Chief Magistrates’ Court sitting in Ore, Ondo State, on Tuesday remanded a man, Peter Moses, in custody for allegedly impregnating his daughter. The 36-year-old man was said to have committed the offence the between November, 2020 and January 2021 in Asewele Korede town in the Odigbo Local Government Area… In "News" Akure  - An Akure Chief Magistrates' Court in Ondo State on Friday remanded a 29 year-old student, Abiodun Adepoju in prison custody for allegedly killing Falilu Bankole,33. The Chief Magistrate, Mrs Victoria Bob-Manuel, ordered the remand of the accused pending legal advice from the state Director of Public Prosecution (DPP).… In "News"